St. Bastbene, the immediate successor of St. Columba, was his first cousin, being son of Brendan, brother of Fedhlimidh¹ He was younger than St. Columba, being only sixty-six years of age at his death, which oc- curred in 599, after a presidency of three years. His acts are preserved in the Codex Salmanti- censis at Brussels (fol. 201), from which they were printed by the Bollandists immediately after those of St. Columba. (minii, tom. ii. pp. 236-238.)
